# SPA fallback for Cloudflare Pages — anything that isn't a real asset gets
# index.html served with a 200, so React Router can handle `/login`,
# `/dashboard/*`, `/auth/callback`, etc. on direct navigation and full reloads.
# Real files (under /assets/*.{js,css,svg,etc.}) are served before this rule
# matches because the static asset handler runs first.
#
# Pattern docs: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
/*    /index.html   200
